blems associated with transmission. David and Alison Quinn examine Richard Hakluyt’s Discourse on Western Planting (1584). I.S. MacLaren investigates the publication, in the nineteenth century, of field notes by Canadian artist Paul Kane. Helen Wallis’s paper looks at the institutionalization of ‘exploration writing’ in the activities of the great publication societies. Finally, in a paper that throws into question assumptions about textuality that would have seemed unassailable three decades ago, James Lockhart examines the textual editing of Nahuatl versions of the conquest of Meso-America. Electronic Format Disclaimer: Images removed at the request of the rights holder.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCriticism, TextualvCongresses. 0aDiscoveries in geographyxSourcesvCongresses. 0aManuscriptsxEditingvCongresses. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Historical & Comparative.2bisacsh1 aB., D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFormisano, Luciano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenige, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLockhart, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacLaren, I. S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQuinn, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWallis, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWarkentin, Germaine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781442623576